comments.body:
Hello,

We tested this issue with the test code below. We canâ€™t reproduce this issue in Ti SDK 3.1.3.GA. It is most likely fixed. Please test this issue using the latest release and let us know your feedback. 

h5. Testing Environment:
Ti CLI 3.1.2
Titanium SDK: 3.1.3 and later 
Titanium SDK 3.1.3 GA
Android SDK: 2.3.3
iOS -Simulator -iPhone Retina 3.5 inch/iOS 7.0.3
Android Device-4.2.2
 
 
 h5. Test Case
 {code}
Titanium.UI.setBackgroundColor('#000');
 
var win1 = Titanium.UI.createWindow({  
    title:'Tab 1',
    backgroundColor:'#fff'
});
 
 
var view = Titanium.UI.createView({	
	 backgroundColor:'red',
	 width:10,
	 height:10
	
});
 
 
var press = Ti.UI.createButton({
	title : 'press',
	height : 'auto',
	width : 'auto',
});
  
press.addEventListener('click', function() {
	view.updateLayout({top:200, left:200});
});
 
view.top = 50;
view.left = 50;
 
win1.add(press);
win1.add(view);
win1.open();
{code}

h5. Steps to Reproduce:
# Create a simple project.
# Update this code in app.js 
# Run this with testing environment
# App will display red view and button
# Click on button for updateLayout effect 
# View position will update  

Thanks
